vulnerability.name: USN-7488-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that Python incorrectly handled parsing bracketed hosts. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to perform a Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) attack. This issue only affected python 2.7 and python3.4 for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS; python2.7 for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS; python2.7, python3.6, python3.7, and python3.8 for Ubuntu 18.04 LTS; python2.7 and python3.9 for Ubuntu 20.04 LTS; and python2.7 and python3.11 for Ubuntu 22.04 LTS. (CVE-2024-11168)  It was discovered that Python allowed excessive backtracking while parsing certain tarfile headers. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause Python to consume resources, leading to a denial of service. This issue only affected python3.4 for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS; python3.6, python3.7, and python3.8 for Ubuntu 18.04 LTS; python3.9 for Ubuntu 20.04 LTS; and python3.11 for Ubuntu 22.04 LTS. (CVE-2024-6232)  It was discovered that Python incorrectly handled quoting path names when using the venv module. A local attacker able to control virtual environments could possibly use this issue to execute arbitrary code when the virtual environment is activated. This issue only affected python3.4 for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS; python3.6, python3.7, and python3.8 for Ubuntu 18.04 LTS; python3.9 for Ubuntu 20.04 LTS; python3.11 for Ubuntu 22.04 LTS; and python3.13 for Ubuntu 24.10. (CVE-2024-9287)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in Python.
